# ============================================================================
# BoeNet Docker Build Context Exclusions (v1.0.1)
# ============================================================================
# This file specifies which files and directories should be excluded from
# the Docker build context to speed up builds and reduce image size.
#
# IMPORTANT: This file MUST be placed in the project ROOT directory
# (same level as train_boenet.py, not inside docker/ folder).
# Docker only reads .dockerignore from the build context root.
#
# Build command (from project root):
#   docker build -t boenet:cuda -f docker/Dockerfile.cuda .
#
# Changelog:
#   v1.0.1 (2025-12-29):
#     - Added data/.cache for HuggingFace cache exclusion
#     - Added .hf_cache for alternative HuggingFace cache location
#     - Added hub/ and datasets/ patterns for HuggingFace artifacts
#     - Fixed Windows long path issues during Docker build
#     - Updated header to clarify root directory requirement
#     - Renamed project references from BFSNet to BoeNet
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HuggingFace Cache (CRITICAL - Prevents Windows Long Path Errors)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HuggingFace downloads create deeply nested directories with long paths
# that cause "invalid file request" errors on Windows Docker builds.
# These MUST be excluded from the build context.

# Primary HuggingFace cache location (v1.0.3 Dockerfile default)
data/.cache
data/.cache/

# Alternative HuggingFace cache locations
.hf_cache
.hf_cache/
.cache/
.cache/huggingface/

# HuggingFace hub artifacts (can appear in various locations)
**/hub/
**/datasets--*/
**/.locks/
**/snapshots/
**/refs/
**/blobs/

